      "title": "Marie Arrives in Paris",
      "content": "Marie stepped off the plane at Charles de Gaulle airport. The excitement of finally being in Paris made her heart race. As she walked through the terminal, she practiced the French phrases she had learned.\n\n\"Bonjour!\" said the immigration officer with a warm smile.\n\n\"Bonjour, monsieur,\" Marie responded, trying to sound confident.\n\n\"Vous êtes américaine?\" he asked, noticing her passport.\n\n\"Oui, je suis américaine. Je m'appelle Marie,\" she said proudly.\n\nThe officer stamped her passport. \"Bienvenue en France! Welcome to France!\"\n\n\"Merci beaucoup!\" Marie said, feeling a rush of accomplishment. Her French was working!\n\nAs she collected her luggage, an elderly French woman accidentally bumped into her.\n\n\"Oh, pardon! Excusez-moi, mademoiselle,\" the woman apologized.\n\n\"Ce n'est pas grave,\" Marie replied, remembering the phrase for \"it's okay.\"\n\nThe woman smiled approvingly. \"Vous parlez très bien français!\"\n\nMarie blushed. She didn't speak French \"very well\" yet, but it was a good start.",
